article.headline: Montana 81, Portland St. 76
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Anthony Johnson scored 22 points to lead Montana to an 81-76 win over Portland State on Friday night. Ryan Staudacher added 18 points for the Grizzlies (18-7, 9-4 Big Sky), while Will Cherry had 13 and Brian Qvale 11. Jamie Jones led Portland State (10-14, 5-6) with 26 points and 12 rebounds. Melvin Jones added 14 points, Julius Thomas 13 and Dominic Waters 12. Montana jumped ahead early and led 11-2 after Staudacher hit a 3-pointer with 14:54 left in the first half. The Grizzlies, who never trailed, led by as many as 15 points in the second half before Portland State came to life. A late 13-3 run closed the gap to 70-67 with 4:07 remaining, but Montana held on down the stretch to sweep the season series. Montana shot 49.1 percent (26 of 53) and Portland State 48.1 percent (26 of 54).
